## 🎯 Phase 1: MVP - Core Audiobook Player (Months 1-4)

**Goal:** Launch a stable, feature-rich audiobook player that rivals commercial apps

### Month 1: Foundation

**Week 1-2: Project Setup & Core Infrastructure**
- [x] Repository initialization
- [x] Rust workspace setup (10+ crates)
- [x] Database schema design (SQLx + migrations)
- [x] Error handling framework
- [x] Build scripts for Windows
- [x] CI/CD pipeline (GitHub Actions)
- [ ] Development environment documentation

**Week 3-4: Media Engine Foundation**
- [ ] Audio format detection system
- [ ] Symphonia integration (multi-format decoder)
- [ ] Basic playback state machine
- [ ] Chapter extraction logic
- [ ] Metadata parsing (MP3, M4A, FLAC, OGG, Opus)
- [ ] Cover art extraction
- [ ] Unit tests for all parsers

**Deliverable:** Working audio decoder that can parse all major formats

### Month 2: Core Features

**Week 1-2: Playback Engine**
- [ ] Complete playback state machine
- [ ] Position tracking (auto-save every 5s)
- [ ] Playback speed control (0.5x - 3.0x)
- [ ] Sleep timer with fade-out
- [ ] Bookmark system
- [ ] Volume control and boost
- [ ] Integration with Android MediaSession

**Week 3-4: Library Management**
- [ ] Filesystem scanner (recursive, async)
- [ ] Manual file import
- [ ] Database operations (CRUD for audiobooks)
- [ ] Search implementation (FTS5)
- [ ] Playlist management
- [ ] Smart playlists (auto-updating)
- [ ] Library statistics

**Deliverable:** Fully functional audiobook player with library management

### Month 3: Streaming & Content Sources

**Week 1-2: Streaming Infrastructure**
